The paper proposes a control-theoretic framework for verification of numerical software systems, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convex optimization techniques, which is a common topic in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the verification of software safety and performance specifications, which is a topic that falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Lyapunov functions, which is a topic that falls under the cs.LO (Optimization and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the absence of overflow and division-by-zero, which are topics that fall under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
